## 12. Enums - Tutorial specs for AI (C++)

### 12.1 Topic - Basic Enums (named integer constants)

- **Exclusions (do not teach or mention in this topic)**
  - Do **not** introduce or reference: `enum class`; `typedef`/`using` aliases; bit flags/bitwise operators; using enums across multiple files; pointer-to-enum; advanced casting.
  - Use only: `enum Name { ... }`, enum variables, comparisons in `if`/`switch`, and printing simple messages (do not teach mapping tables yet).

```cpp
// 1. Basic enum for days
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

enum Day { MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY };

int main() {
    Day today = WEDNESDAY;
    cout << "Today (as number) = " << today << "\n";
    if (today == FRIDAY) {
        cout << "Weekend soon!\n";
    }
    return 0;
}
```

```cpp
// 2. Enum with explicit values
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

enum Status { STATUS_OK = 1, STATUS_WARNING = 2, STATUS_ERROR = 3 };

int main() {
    Status s = STATUS_WARNING;
    if (s == STATUS_WARNING) {
        cout << "Warning!\n";
    }
    return 0;
}
```

```cpp
// 3. Using enum for menu choice
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

enum MenuOption { MENU_ADD = 1, MENU_SUB = 2, MENU_MUL = 3, MENU_EXIT = 4 };

int main() {
    int choice;
    cout << "1. Add\n2. Sub\n3. Mul\n4. Exit\n";
    cout << "Enter choice: ";
    cin >> choice;

    if (choice == MENU_EXIT) {
        cout << "Goodbye\n";
    } else {
        cout << "You chose: " << choice << "\n";
    }
    return 0;
}
```

